SCRIPTING BEGINNER CONCEPTS:


a script file in Windows ends with the prefix .ps1
  example: HelloWorld.ps1

to run a file, go to powershell prompt and type: ./<filename>.ps1
  example:  ./HelloWorld.ps1

commenting - single line:
  #COMMENT_GOES_HERE

single output line:
  Write-Output 'This is your statement'

example - hello world program
  make a file called HelloWorld.ps1

  Write-Output 'Hello World!'
  # yes, its ok to include spaces!
